{"id":234317,"date":"2024-01-30T18:18:49","date_gmt":"2024-01-30T12:48:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=234317"},"modified":"2024-01-30T18:18:49","modified_gmt":"2024-01-30T12:48:49","slug":"samir-shah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/","title":{"rendered":"Samir Shah Wiki, Age, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-235826\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah.jpg\" alt=\"Samir Shah\" width=\"520\" height=\"376\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah.jpg 830w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-300x217.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-768x555.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Samir Shah is a British (of Indian origin) journalist and TV and radio host. He is the Chairman of BBC (British Broadcasting Corporation). He is the owner, CEO, and creative director of Juniper TV Limited.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce0389bf88\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce0389bf88\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Physical_Appearance\" title=\"Physical Appearance\">Physical Appearance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Family\" title=\"Family\">Family<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Parents_Siblings\" title=\"Parents &amp; Siblings\">Parents &amp; Siblings<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Wife_Children\" title=\"Wife &amp; Children\">Wife &amp; Children<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Religion\" title=\"Religion\">Religion<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#BBC\" title=\"BBC\u00a0\">BBC\u00a0<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#BBC_Chair\" title=\"BBC Chair\">BBC Chair<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Juniper_TV\" title=\"Juniper TV\">Juniper TV<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Television\" title=\"Television\">Television<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Writing\" title=\"Writing\">Writing<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Positions_of_Responsibility\" title=\"Positions of Responsibility\">Positions of Responsibility<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-14\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Controversies\" title=\"Controversies\">Controversies<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-15\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Criticism_Over_Being_Chosen_As_BBC_Chair\" title=\"Criticism Over Being Chosen As BBC Chair\">Criticism Over Being Chosen As BBC Chair<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-16\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#%E2%80%9CWhat_British_Muslims_Really_Think%E2%80%9D_Documentary\" title=\"&#8220;What British Muslims Really Think&#8221; Documentary\">&#8220;What British Muslims Really Think&#8221; Documentary<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-17\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#The_Commission_On_Race_And_Ethnic_Disparities\" title=\"The Commission On Race And Ethnic Disparities\">The Commission On Race And Ethnic Disparities<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-18\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Awards_Honours_Achievements\" title=\"Awards, Honours, Achievements\">Awards, Honours, Achievements<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-19\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/samir-shah\/#Salary\" title=\"Salary\">Salary<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span>Wiki\/Biography<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Samir Shah CBE (the title CBE denotes Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire) was born on Tuesday, 29 January 1952 (<strong>age 72 years; as of 2024<\/strong>) in Aurangabad (renamed as Chhatrapati Sambhaji Nagar in 2023), Maharashtra, India. His zodiac sign is Aquarius. Samir studied at the Latymer Upper School in West London, England. He pursued a bachelor&#8217;s degree in Economics at the University of Hull (formerly, University College Hull) in England. In 1979, he received a DPhil in Anthropology and Geography from St Catherine&#8217;s College, University of Oxford. His thesis was on the &#8220;Aspects of the geographic analysis of Asian immigrants in London&#8221;.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235853\" style=\"width: 473px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-during-his-younger-days.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235853\" class=\" wp-image-235853\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-during-his-younger-days.jpg\" alt=\"Samir Shah during his younger days\" width=\"463\" height=\"327\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-during-his-younger-days.jpg 849w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-during-his-younger-days-300x212.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-during-his-younger-days-768x543.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 463px) 100vw, 463px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235853\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Samir Shah during his younger days<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Physical_Appearance\"><\/span>Physical Appearance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong>Height (approx.):<\/strong> 5&#8242; 7&#8243;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Hair Colour:\u00a0<\/strong>Grey<\/p>\n<p><strong>Eye Colour:\u00a0<\/strong>Brown<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family\"><\/span>Family<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>In 1960, Samir Shah and his family moved from India to England.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parents_Siblings\"><\/span><strong>Parents &amp; Siblings<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>His father&#8217;s name is Amrit Shah. His mother&#8217;s name is Uma Bakaya, a mathematician. Amrit and Uma broke their marriage after moving to England, and Uma married Madan Bakaya. Madan is Shah&#8217;s stepfather and worked as a production manager in Bollywood. Shah has an elder sister, Monisha Shah, who was Director of Emerging Markets at BBC Worldwide.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235830\" style=\"width: 227px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Monisha-Shah-Samir-Shahs-elder-sister.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235830\" class=\" wp-image-235830\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Monisha-Shah-Samir-Shahs-elder-sister.jpg\" alt=\"Monisha Shah, Samir Shah's elder sister\" width=\"217\" height=\"398\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Monisha-Shah-Samir-Shahs-elder-sister.jpg 327w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Monisha-Shah-Samir-Shahs-elder-sister-164x300.jpg 164w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 217px) 100vw, 217px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235830\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Monisha Shah, Samir Shah&#8217;s elder sister<\/p><\/div>\n<p>He has a stepbrother named Mohit Bakaya, who is Shah&#8217;s mother&#8217;s son with Madan. Mohit is a radio producer and controller of BBC Radio 4.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235834\" style=\"width: 451px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Mohit-Bakaya-Samir-Shahs-stepbrother.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235834\" class=\" wp-image-235834\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Mohit-Bakaya-Samir-Shahs-stepbrother.jpg\" alt=\"Mohit Bakaya, Samir Shah's stepbrother\" width=\"441\" height=\"317\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Mohit-Bakaya-Samir-Shahs-stepbrother.jpg 836w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Mohit-Bakaya-Samir-Shahs-stepbrother-300x215.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Mohit-Bakaya-Samir-Shahs-stepbrother-768x551.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 441px) 100vw, 441px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235834\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Mohit Bakaya, Samir Shah&#8217;s stepbrother<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Wife_Children\"><\/span><strong>Wife &amp; Children<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Samir is married to Belkis. She is a major shareholder of Juniper TV. The couple have a son.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Religion\"><\/span>Religion<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Samir Shah followed Jainism when he was in India. Later, in England, he converted to Islam to marry his wife, Belkis.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span>Career<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"BBC\"><\/span><strong>BBC\u00a0<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Shah joined the London Weekend Television in 1979 as a researcher. Here, he worked with influential people like John Brit and Micheal Wills. In 1987 he was appointed as BBC&#8217;s (British Broadcasting Corporation) head of television current affairs. From 1994 to 1998, he was appointed as the head of political journalism programmes at BBC. In 1998, he left BBC and stated that the reason behind this was connected to an executives&#8217; residential course at the London Business School, University of London. Shah returned to BBC. From 2007 to 2010, he served as the BBC board&#8217;s non-executive director.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"BBC_Chair\"><\/span><strong>BBC Chair<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>While BBC is politically independent, the government of the UK is in charge of appointing the BBC Chair. In December 2023, the Culture Secretary from the Department for Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) announced Shah to be the government&#8217;s choice for BBC Chair.<\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\">\n<p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Culture Secretary <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/lucyfrazermp?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">@LucyFrazerMP<\/a> has announced Dr Samir Shah CBE as Government\u2019s preferred candidate for the BBC Chair<\/p>\n<p>The Culture Secretary also thanked Dame Elan Closs Stephens for her work as Acting Chair<\/p>\n<p>Find out more: <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/48VVxfVo0Q\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https:\/\/t.co\/48VVxfVo0Q<\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/nsU5xXjeKq\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">pic.twitter.com\/nsU5xXjeKq<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&mdash; Department for Culture, Media and Sport (@DCMS) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/DCMS\/status\/1732402027823567080?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">December 6, 2023<\/a><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script><\/p>\n<p>In response to his nomination, Shah put out an announcement in which he said,<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>If I am able to put what skills, experience, and understanding of public service broadcasting I have built up during my career to help this brilliant organisation meet the complex and diverse challenges it faces over the coming years, it would be an honour.&#8221; <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_234317_1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_234317_1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/indianexpress.com\/article\/world\/samir-shah-new-bbc-chairman-aurangabad-uk-9057976\/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">The Indian Express<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>Before his appointment, Shah attended a &#8220;pre-appointment scrutiny&#8221; (a hearing) with MPs from the Culture, Media and Sport Select Committee. At the pre-appointment scrutiny, a few MPs put out a statement criticising Shah&#8217;s ability to be the Chair of BBC. The media committee of the House of Commons put out a statement saying Shah was &#8220;appointable as Chair&#8221;. As Chair, Shah has to work for 3-4 days a week.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235738\" style=\"width: 517px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-the-pre-appointment-scrutiny-in-the-House-of-Commons-in-2023.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235738\" class=\" wp-image-235738\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-the-pre-appointment-scrutiny-in-the-House-of-Commons-in-2023.jpg\" alt=\"Samir Shah at the pre-appointment scrutiny in the House of Commons in 2023\" width=\"507\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-the-pre-appointment-scrutiny-in-the-House-of-Commons-in-2023.jpg 1009w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-the-pre-appointment-scrutiny-in-the-House-of-Commons-in-2023-300x178.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-the-pre-appointment-scrutiny-in-the-House-of-Commons-in-2023-768x457.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 507px) 100vw, 507px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235738\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Samir Shah at the pre-appointment scrutiny in the House of Commons in 2023<\/p><\/div>\n<p>One responsibility that Samir Shah holds as BBC Chair is dealing with the renewal of BBC&#8217;s charter in 2027.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Juniper_TV\"><\/span><strong>Juniper TV<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Samir Shah bought Juniper TV Ltd., a commercial production company, from Micheal Wills whom he used to work with in London Weekend Television. He did this after leaving BBC in 1998 and after Micheal Wills was appointed as a Member of Parliament. Shah is the CEO and creative director of Juniper TV, which is an independent TV and radio production company. Juniper TV puts out documentaries and current affairs programmes. The programmes put out by Juniper are screened on various media platforms including the BBC, Channel 4, National Geographic, Discovery, TLC, and Netflix.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235812\" style=\"width: 422px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-logo-of-Samir-Shahs-production-company-Juniper-TV.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235812\" class=\" wp-image-235812\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-logo-of-Samir-Shahs-production-company-Juniper-TV.jpg\" alt=\"The logo of Samir Shah's production company, Juniper TV\" width=\"412\" height=\"229\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-logo-of-Samir-Shahs-production-company-Juniper-TV.jpg 1081w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-logo-of-Samir-Shahs-production-company-Juniper-TV-300x167.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-logo-of-Samir-Shahs-production-company-Juniper-TV-1024x568.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-logo-of-Samir-Shahs-production-company-Juniper-TV-768x426.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235812\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The logo of Samir Shah&#8217;s production company, Juniper TV<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Television\"><\/span><strong>Television<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Samir Shah has worked as a writer, producer, and executive producer for documentaries and television series. He wrote the drama documentary named &#8220;Theresa vs. Boris: How May Became PM&#8221; (2017).<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235815\" style=\"width: 321px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-poster-of-Theresa-vs.-Boris-How-May-Became-PM-a-documentary-written-by-Samir-Shah.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235815\" class=\" wp-image-235815\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-poster-of-Theresa-vs.-Boris-How-May-Became-PM-a-documentary-written-by-Samir-Shah.jpg\" alt=\"The poster of Theresa vs. Boris: How May Became PM, a documentary written by Samir Shah\" width=\"311\" height=\"458\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-poster-of-Theresa-vs.-Boris-How-May-Became-PM-a-documentary-written-by-Samir-Shah.jpg 407w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/The-poster-of-Theresa-vs.-Boris-How-May-Became-PM-a-documentary-written-by-Samir-Shah-204x300.jpg 204w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235815\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The poster of Theresa vs. Boris: How May Became PM, a documentary written by Samir Shah<\/p><\/div>\n<p>He was the producer for five episodes of the TV series &#8220;Eastern Eye&#8221; (1982 to 1985). He has been the executive producer of programmes such as &#8220;Thatcher: The Downing Street Years&#8221; (1993), &#8220;Fire, Plague, War and Treason&#8221; (2001), &#8220;The Great British Black Invasion&#8221; (2006), &#8220;Sir Alex Ferguson: Secrets of Success&#8221; (2015), and &#8220;This Week&#8221; (2019).<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Writing\"><\/span><strong>Writing<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Samir Shah co-authored the UK government&#8217;s report on the Commission on Race and Ethnic Disparities in 2021. The UK government ordered the report to be made in light of the Black Lives Matter protests in 2020. According to the report, there was no institutional racism in the UK.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235822\" style=\"width: 507px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-right-giving-an-interview-about-the-UK-governments-report-on-the-Commission-on-Race-and-Ethnic-Disparities-on-the-LBC-Studio-news-service.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235822\" class=\" wp-image-235822\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-right-giving-an-interview-about-the-UK-governments-report-on-the-Commission-on-Race-and-Ethnic-Disparities-on-the-LBC-Studio-news-service.jpg\" alt=\"Samir Shah (right) giving an interview about the UK government's report on the Commission on Race and Ethnic Disparities on the LBC Studio news service\" width=\"497\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-right-giving-an-interview-about-the-UK-governments-report-on-the-Commission-on-Race-and-Ethnic-Disparities-on-the-LBC-Studio-news-service.jpg 1083w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-right-giving-an-interview-about-the-UK-governments-report-on-the-Commission-on-Race-and-Ethnic-Disparities-on-the-LBC-Studio-news-service-300x166.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-right-giving-an-interview-about-the-UK-governments-report-on-the-Commission-on-Race-and-Ethnic-Disparities-on-the-LBC-Studio-news-service-1024x567.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-right-giving-an-interview-about-the-UK-governments-report-on-the-Commission-on-Race-and-Ethnic-Disparities-on-the-LBC-Studio-news-service-768x425.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 497px) 100vw, 497px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235822\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Samir Shah (right) giving an interview about the UK government&#8217;s report on the Commission on Race and Ethnic Disparities on the LBC Studio news service<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Positions_of_Responsibility\"><\/span><strong>Positions of Responsibility<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Samir Shah was the Chairman of the Runnymede Trust from 1999\u20132009. He was the trustee (2005-2014) and Deputy Chairman (2012-14) of the Victoria and Albert Museum in London. From 2006 to 2017, Shah was a special professor in the Post Conflict Studies department at the University of Nottingham, England. From 2014 to 2022, he served as the Chairman of the Museum of the Home in London. In 2019, Shah was a visiting professor (faculty of English) of Creative Media at the University of Oxford. He was a board member of BAFTA (British Academy of Film and Television Arts) and a commissioner on the HMG Commission on Race and Ethnic Disparities. In 2014, Shah joined as a member of the PM Holocaust Commission for one year. He was a member of the Cultural Recovery Board from 2020\u201321 and the Heritage Advisory Board in 2020. In 2020, he also became Chair of the trustee board for One World Media. In 2021, he was a Future of Public Service Broadcasting member.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Controversies\"><\/span>Controversies<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Criticism_Over_Being_Chosen_As_BBC_Chair\"><\/span><strong>Criticism Over Being Chosen As BBC Chair<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>When Samir Shah was announced as the government&#8217;s preferred candidate for BBC chair, Members of Parliament (House of Commons) mentioned their reservations about his appointment. At Shah&#8217;s pre-appointment scrutiny, the MPs submitted a report stating that they doubted Shah&#8217;s ability to &#8220;provide robust challenge to its leadership&#8221;. Here, leadership refers to the executive leaders at BBC. They stated that Shah did not showcase the strength and character required to question BBC&#8217;s executive leadership. In the report submitted by the MPs, they stated that they were,<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>disappointed that Dr Shah was not willing to express a view on fundamental principles, such as board-level interference in the BBC and other bodies and on political impartiality.&#8221; <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_234317_1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_234317_1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.theguardian.com\/media\/2023\/dec\/15\/mps-raise-concerns-over-government-choice-of-samir-shah-as-bbc-chair#:~:text=MPs%20raise%20concerns%20over%20government%20choice%20of%20Samir%20Shah%20as%20BBC%20chair,-This%20article%20is&amp;text=MP%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about,robust%20challenge%20to%20its%20leadership%E2%80%9D.\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">The Guardian<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>The MPs demanded that Shah needed to address BBC&#8217;s pressing issues and provide better answers for how he would deal with such issues. They said.<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>It is now for the government to consider whether to go ahead with the appointment. If they decide to proceed, we expect Dr Shah to appear before us in the new year to demonstrate he has addressed our concerns.&#8221; <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_234317_1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_234317_1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.theguardian.com\/media\/2023\/dec\/15\/mps-raise-concerns-over-government-choice-of-samir-shah-as-bbc-chair#:~:text=MPs%20raise%20concerns%20over%20government%20choice%20of%20Samir%20Shah%20as%20BBC%20chair,-This%20article%20is&amp;text=MP%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about,robust%20challenge%20to%20its%20leadership%E2%80%9D.\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">The Guardian<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>Shah also received negative comments from internet users who criticised him for allegedly working for and having connections with the ruling Conservative party. The Department for Culture, Media and Sport supported Shah and stated that he was suited for the role due to his extensive experience in TV production and journalism.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"%E2%80%9CWhat_British_Muslims_Really_Think%E2%80%9D_Documentary\"><\/span><strong>&#8220;What British Muslims Really Think&#8221; Documentary<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>In 2016, Shah was the executive producer of a documentary made under Juniper TV named &#8220;What British Muslims Really Think&#8221;. Trevor Phillips hosted the documentary which received over 200 complaints. The documentary claimed to present a thorough survey of British Muslims&#8217; views. It faced controversy for commissioning a poll indicating that more than half of British Muslims believe homosexuality should be illegal. Ofcom (UK&#8217;s Office of Communications) received 89 complaints, and Channel 4 reported receiving around 130 complaints and 20 messages supportive of the program. People stated their concern over misinformation and the potential to fuel Islamophobia.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235840\" style=\"width: 582px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Trevor-Phillips-in-What-do-Muslims-Really-Think-a-documentary-for-which-Samir-Shah-was-executive-producer.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235840\" class=\" wp-image-235840\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Trevor-Phillips-in-What-do-Muslims-Really-Think-a-documentary-for-which-Samir-Shah-was-executive-producer.jpg\" alt=\"Trevor Phillips in 'What do Muslims Really Think', a documentary for which Samir Shah was executive producer\" width=\"572\" height=\"356\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Trevor-Phillips-in-What-do-Muslims-Really-Think-a-documentary-for-which-Samir-Shah-was-executive-producer.jpg 964w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Trevor-Phillips-in-What-do-Muslims-Really-Think-a-documentary-for-which-Samir-Shah-was-executive-producer-300x187.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Trevor-Phillips-in-What-do-Muslims-Really-Think-a-documentary-for-which-Samir-Shah-was-executive-producer-768x478.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 572px) 100vw, 572px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235840\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Trevor Phillips in &#8216;What do Muslims Really Think&#8217;, a documentary for which Samir Shah was executive producer<\/p><\/div>\n<p>People also criticised the documentary&#8217;s surveying methods and the areas in Britain that were surveyed. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_234317_1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_234317_1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.aljazeera.com\/opinions\/2016\/4\/14\/beware-of-what-british-muslims-really-think\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Aljazeera<\/a><\/span><\/span> A Guardian panel of British Muslims criticized the show as &#8220;boring, inaccurate, and sensationalist&#8221; and stated that their method was &#8220;problematic.&#8221; Ofcom was in charge of assessing the complaints before deciding on a full investigation. Channel 4 put out a statement where they defended the programme&#8217;s integrity, and stated that they were committed to representing the minority&#8217;s views with responsibility. Shah refused to give any statement on the controversy.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"The_Commission_On_Race_And_Ethnic_Disparities\"><\/span><strong>The Commission On Race And Ethnic Disparities<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>In 2021, Samir Shah, a part of the Commission on Race and Ethnic Disparities, co-authored a report with the UK government. Several activists, organisations, and people on the internet strongly criticised the findings of the report. According to the UN Working Group of Experts on People of African Descent, the report denied the existence of institutional racism, disregarded complex race analyses, and discredited data on racism. The report also gave an inaccurate history of slavery and ignored the UK&#8217;s racial inequality. The report was also criticised for normalising white supremacy. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_234317_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_234317_1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_234317_1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ohchr.org\/en\/press-releases\/2021\/04\/un-experts-condemn-uk-commission-race-and-ethnic-disparities-report\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">United Nations<\/a><\/span><\/span> Shah defended the report during a BBC interview.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235865\" style=\"width: 544px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-on-BBC-defending-the-UK-governments-race-report-that-he-co-authored.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235865\" class=\" wp-image-235865\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-on-BBC-defending-the-UK-governments-race-report-that-he-co-authored.jpg\" alt=\"Samir Shah, on BBC, defending the UK government's race report that he co-authored\" width=\"534\" height=\"252\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-on-BBC-defending-the-UK-governments-race-report-that-he-co-authored.jpg 1272w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-on-BBC-defending-the-UK-governments-race-report-that-he-co-authored-300x142.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-on-BBC-defending-the-UK-governments-race-report-that-he-co-authored-1024x483.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-on-BBC-defending-the-UK-governments-race-report-that-he-co-authored-768x362.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 534px) 100vw, 534px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235865\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Samir Shah, on BBC, defending the UK government&#8217;s race report that he co-authored<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Awards_Honours_Achievements\"><\/span>Awards, Honours, Achievements<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Samir Shah was appointed OBE (Most Excellent Order of the British Empire) in 1999, &#8220;for services to equal opportunities in broadcasting&#8221;.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2002, Samir Shah was made a Fellow of the Royal Television Society.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>For his services to television and heritage, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/queen-elizabeth-ii\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Queen Elizabeth II<\/a> presented Samir Shah with the CBE (Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire) in 2019.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_235759\" style=\"width: 547px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-an-interview-after-receiving-the-CBE-Commander-of-the-Most-Excellent-Order-of-the-British-Empire-in-2019.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235759\" class=\" wp-image-235759\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-an-interview-after-receiving-the-CBE-Commander-of-the-Most-Excellent-Order-of-the-British-Empire-in-2019.jpg\" alt=\"Samir Shah at an interview after receiving the CBE (Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire) in 2019\" width=\"537\" height=\"383\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-an-interview-after-receiving-the-CBE-Commander-of-the-Most-Excellent-Order-of-the-British-Empire-in-2019.jpg 842w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-an-interview-after-receiving-the-CBE-Commander-of-the-Most-Excellent-Order-of-the-British-Empire-in-2019-300x214.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Samir-Shah-at-an-interview-after-receiving-the-CBE-Commander-of-the-Most-Excellent-Order-of-the-British-Empire-in-2019-768x547.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 537px) 100vw, 537px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235759\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Samir Shah at an interview after receiving the CBE (Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire) in 2019<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>For providing his services for over 40 years and his commitment towards diversity in the TV industry, Samir Shah received the Outstanding Contribution Award from the Royal Television Society in 2022.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Salary\"><\/span>Salary<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Samir Shah&#8217;s salary as BBC Chair is \u00a3 1,60,000 per annum.<\/p>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:b